modules.description: This module provides direct serialization and deserialization of Cstruct buffers and Cstruct values to and from S-expressions. It supports converting raw memory buffers and structured Cstruct values into S-expressions using `sexp_of_buffer` and `sexp_of_t`, and reconstructing them with `buffer_of_sexp` and `t_of_sexp`. Concrete use cases include persisting binary data structures to disk, transmitting structured memory buffers over networks, and embedding binary payloads in configuration files or logs.
